
---


@startuml

' Entities
class Patient {
  +id: int
  +name: string
  +consentGiven: boolean
  +treatments: Set<Treatment>
}

class Doctor {
  +id: int
  +name: string
  +diagnoses: Set<Diagnosis>
}

class HeadDoctor {
  +id: int
  +name: string
  +approveDiagnosis(diagnosis: Diagnosis): boolean
}

class Illness {
  +id: int
  +name: string
  +priority: Priority
  +treatments: Set<Treatment>
}

enum Priority {
  HIGH
  LOW
}

class Diagnosis {
  +id: int
  +patient: Patient
  +doctor: Doctor
  +illness: Illness
  +approvedByHeadDoctor: boolean
}

class Treatment {
  +id: int
  +illness: Illness
  +stage: Stage
  +patient: Patient
  +consentGiven: boolean
}

enum Stage {
  STAGE_1
  STAGE_2
  STAGE_3
}

' Associations
Patient "1" -- "0..*" Treatment : has
Doctor "1" -- "0..*" Diagnosis : makes
HeadDoctor "1" -- "0..*" Diagnosis : approves
Illness "1" -- "0..*" Diagnosis : relates to
Illness "1" -- "0..*" Treatment : has
Treatment "1" -- "1" Patient : applies to
Diagnosis "1" -- "1" Illness : related to
Diagnosis "1" -- "1" Doctor : made by
Diagnosis "1" -- "1" Patient : for

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:
- The `Priority` and `Stage` enums represent the possible states of an illness and a treatment.
- A patient can have multiple treatments, each with a stage.
- A doctor can make multiple diagnoses, and a diagnosis must be approved by the head doctor before any treatment can proceed.
- If an illness has a **high priority**, all associated treatments are immediately moved to **Stage 3**, regardless of consent.
- Once a patient gives consent, all treatments can be upgraded to higher stages without further consent.

